# Verify-grep exclusions — read by the bootstrap verify step (`/bootstrap` § Verify
# and bootstrap/SETUP.md § Verify) via `grep -vE -f` after stripping comment and
# blank lines. One extended-regex pattern per line, matched against the verify
# grep's `path:line:token` output. Patterns must anchor path segments with (^|/) —
# a bare leading slash silently fails on greps that emit unprefixed paths (ugrep
# and other drop-in replacements).
#
# The kit's own exclusions ship below: bootstrap/** documents the tokens,
# README.md files may cite them, and the meta-literal tokens are illustrative
# (see PLACEHOLDERS.md § Meta-literals). Do not remove them.
#
# Retrofit repos: append patterns for pre-existing RUNTIME placeholders that are
# not kit tokens — templating your own scripts fill at run time, e.g. a report
# template's {{DATE}}/{{FEATURE}}:
#   (^|/)ai/TEMPLATES/.*_REPORT_TEMPLATE\.md
# Keep each pattern as narrow as the real exception; this file is the accepted
# list, so a broad pattern can hide a genuinely unfilled token.
(^|/)bootstrap/
(^|/)README\.md
\{\{(TOKEN|TOKENS|PLACEHOLDER|DOUBLE_BRACE)\}\}
